note.body:
I am running into the same issue as Alexander. I have been looking through some of the source code (goadaemon.c), and I think I see what could be a part of the issue. In the "add_config_file" method, there is a section that removes old temp accounts. The issue comes in this if statement:

```
if (provider == NULL)
                    {
                      g_warning ("Unsupported account type %s for ID %s (no provider)", provider_type, id);
                      goto cleanup_and_continue;
                    }
```

As you can see it checks to see if the provider is null (which of course it is), and then throws out that message that thoroughly clogs up the logs. The issue that I see is that this does not remove this temporary account, so when the method is run again, it will continue to do the same thing over and over again.

Is there any way to manually remove these accounts, or clear wherever it is reading these expired accounts from?
